Responsibilities：

 1. Take ownership of partnerships with one or more major e-commerce platforms in the West Europe region (e.g. Xiaomi Official store, Amazon, Bol.com, belsimpel.nl, Joybuy, Temu, Tiktok, etc. );
 2. Develop and maintain strong relationships with key players in the local e-commerce ecosystem and drive sales growth;
 3. Lead cross-functional projects and handle daily e-commerce operations;
 4. Oversee traffic growth initiatives, including SEO, affiliate marketing, and performance marketing programs, to maximize visibility and conversion;




Requirements：

 1. Proven experience in e-commerce, key account management or related roles;
 2. Strong project management skills, with the ability to multitask across teams and meet sale goals;
 3. Fluent in English, proficiency in Chinese or Dutch is a significant advantage;
 4. Ideally willing to relocate to Düsseldorf, Germany.

